value: <l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">The <rs type="object" ref="../resources/annotations.xml#obj-pill">pilliwinks</rs> were applied to her, how she had sailed</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">in a [sieve?] singing, how she had raised a storm in the</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">north sea & sunk the kings ships. The great house was not</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">silent then. In <del>the</del> <del>tries</del> There were [birds? bodies?] in the trees,</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">a deep murmur of old forgotten things humming in the</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">mind. And down the roads came the wandering singer,</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">lewd, impudent; but to <rs type="person" ref="../resources/annotations.xml#psn-espe" key="Spenser, Edmund">Spensers</rs> ear: but <del>he had seen,</del></l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">who had seen, at the Green players acting his already</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">past before <rs type="person" ref="../resources/annotations.xml#psn-eliz" key="Elizabeth I">Queen Elizabeth</rs>.</l>
